eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 40 Years
Maximum age: 40 Years

Subjects with any malignant solid tumor without intracranial involvement or
             metastases diagnosed by standard pathology criteria that has failed standard
             chemotherapy.
Patients must be in first CR/VGPR
Patients with chronic conditions associated with non-malignant abnormal bone growth (e.g., Paget’s disease of bone)

Clinically significant heart disease (e.g., congestive heart failure of New York
             Heart Association Class III or IV, angina not well controlled by medication, or
             myocardial infarction within 6 months).

groups.description: Patients receive paclitaxel IV over 1-2 hours on days 1, 8, and 15 and nintedanib PO BID on days 2-7, 9-14, and 16-28. Courses repeat every 28 days in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Treatment (paclitaxel, nintedanib)

groups.description: Previously collected bone marrow aspirates from patients undergo density gradient centrifugation. Stromal cells are isolated from the otherwise discarded red blood cell layer of the aspirate after density gradient centrifugation. Previously collected bone marrow aspirates from healthy controls undergo density gradient centrifugation. Stromal cells are isolated from the mononuclear cell layer (buffy coat) using conventional means. The stromal cells are then cultured and characterized via flow cytometry and gene expression profiles. Characteristics of cell growth and kinetics for experimental and control stromal cells are studied and compared including morphology, doubling time, time to first passage, number of passages before senescence, etc.
groups.name: Ancillary-Correlative (stromal cell isolation)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Plasma concentrations at serial time points following administration; maximum plasma concentration (Cmax), time to Cmax (Tmax), area under the blood concentration-time curve from time zero to 24 hours (AUC0-24), AUC (0-infinity), terminal half-life (t1/2), clearance (Cl), and volume distribution (Vd); and bioavailability will be measured.
outcome_measures.time_frame: Baseline, 30 minutes, 1, 2, 4, 6, 8, 12, and 24 hours post dose of day 1
